            <h1>
                <a id="about" class="anchor" href="#about" aria-hidden="true">
                    <span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span>
                </a>
                About
            </h1>
            <p>
                This plugin splits <a href="http://www.w3.org/Style/CSS/">CSS</a> stylesheets to smaller files ("parts") which contain maximum
                <a href="split-mojo.html#maxRules">X</a> rules. It uses <a href="http://cssparser.sourceforge.net/">CSS&nbsp;Parser</a> to parse
                source code.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="http://cssparser.sourceforge.net/">CSS Parser</a> supports following standards:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/Style/CSS/">Cascading Style Sheets Level 3</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/">Cascading Style Sheets Level 2 Revision 1 (CSS 2.1) Specification</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2008/REC-CSS2-20080411/">Cascading Style Sheets Level 2</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS1/">Cascading Style Sheets Level 1</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                For more information read the <a href="%RELEASE_VERSION%/split-mojo.html">split</a> goal documentation or take a look into
                <a href="#examples">examples</a>.
            </p>
            <h1>
                <a id="goals-overview" class="anchor" href="#goals-overview" aria-hidden="true">
                    <span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span>
                </a>
                Goals Overview
            </h1>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a href="%RELEASE_VERSION%/split-mojo.html">css-splitter:split</a> - splits <a href="http://www.w3.org/Style/CSS/">CSS</a> stylesheets to
                    smaller files ("parts") which contain maximum <a href="%RELEASE_VERSION%/split-mojo.html#maxRules">X</a> rules
                </li>
            </ul>
