            <h1>
                <a id="download" class="anchor" href="#download" aria-hidden="true">
                    <span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span>
                </a>
                Download
            </h1>
            <p>
                You can download the plugin from docs pages or using various dependency management tools:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://maven.apache.org/">Apache Maven</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://buildr.apache.org/">Apache Buildr</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://ant.apache.org/ivy/">Apache Ivy</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://docs.groovy-lang.org/latest/html/documentation/grape.html">Groovy Grape</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://gradle.org/">Gradle</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://grails.org/">Grails</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://www.scala-sbt.org/">Scala SBT</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://leiningen.org/">Leiningen</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p>Example for Maven:</p>
            <pre>&lt;project&gt;
   ...
   &lt;build&gt;
      &lt;plugins&gt;
         ...
         &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;biz.gabrys.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;css-splitter-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;%RELEASE_VERSION%&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;executions&gt;
               &lt;execution&gt;
                  &lt;id&gt;default-split&lt;/id&gt;
                  &lt;goals&gt;
                     &lt;goal&gt;split&lt;/goal&gt;
                  &lt;/goals&gt;
                  &lt;configuration&gt;
                     &lt;!-- put your configurations here --&gt;
                  &lt;/configuration&gt;
               &lt;/execution&gt;
            &lt;/executions&gt;
         &lt;/plugin&gt;
      &lt;/plugins&gt;
   &lt;/build&gt;
&lt;project&gt;</pre>
